7 Both levels", "align": "center"}, {"type": "key_takeaways", "points": ["**Continuous operation** \u2014 Requirements Management is NOT executed at a specific time; it runs in parallel with all active ADM phases", "**Traceability chain** \u2014 unbroken, bidirectional traceability from top-level vision and strategic goals down to lowest technical requirement", "**On-demand processing** \u2014 captures and processes new requirements identified during any ADM phase or sub-phase", "**Fact invalidation** \u2014 when new facts conflict with existing data, the traceability chain identifies exactly which baseline assumptions are impacted", "Every stakeholder preference must be recorded alongside the literal downstream architectural implications of those choices"]}, {"type": "flashcard_deck", "accent": "#ec4899", "label_front": "DELIVERABLE", "label_back": "PURPOSE", "cards": [{"front": "Requirements Impact Assessment", "back": "A rolling assessment generated when new requirements change existing baselines. Identifies which ADM phases must be revisited and maps full implications on cost, timelines, and business metrics."}, {"front": "Architecture Requirements Specification", "back": "A formal collection of highly quantitative statements that outline exactly what an implementation project must build to comply with the architecture framework."}]}]}]}, {"id": "support", "label": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Frameworks", "color": "#8b5cf6", "slides": [{"id": "repository", "label": "\ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f Repository", "blocks": [{"type": "dark_hero", "heading": "TOGAF Architecture Repository \u2014 8 Classes", "subtext": "Know all eight classes and what each stores \u2014 high-weight exam topic", "badge": "High weight \u00b7 Both levels", "align": "center"}, {"type": "flashcard_deck", "accent": "#8b5cf6", "label_front": "CLASS", "label_back": "WHAT IT STORES", "cards": [{"front": "Architecture Metamodel", "back": "The framework defining the organizationally tailored application of the framework \u2014 precise method and content metadata rules."}, {"front": "Architecture Capability", "back": "The parameters, structural roles, and processes supporting governance and operation of the repository itself."}, {"front": "Architecture Landscape", "back": "The architectural representation of operational or planned enterprise assets at specific points in time."}, {"front": "Standards Library", "back": "Authoritative catalog of mandated standards (industry criteria, product selections, shared services) that new architectures must strictly comply with."}, {"front": "Reference Library", "back": "Guidelines, templates, and reusable patterns leveraged to accelerate domain architecture creation."}, {"front": "Governance Repository", "back": "Historical record of all governance activities, Board decisions, and compliance reviews across the enterprise."}, {"front": "Architecture Requirements Repository", "back": "Central view of all authorized architecture requirements currently agreed upon with the Architecture Board."}, {"front": "Solutions Landscape", "back": "The architectural representation of physical Solution Building Blocks (SBBs) deployed to support the landscape."}]}]}, {"id": "landscape-abbs", "label": "\ud83c\udfd4\ufe0f Landscape & ABBs", "blocks": [{"type": "dark_hero", "heading": "Landscape Levels \u00b7 ABBs vs SBBs \u00b7 Gap Analysis", "subtext": "Three of the highest-weight supporting framework topics", "badge": "High weight \u00b7 Both levels", "align": "center"}, {"type": "flashcard_deck", "accent": "#8b5cf6", "label_front": "LEVEL", "label_back": "DEFINITION", "cards": [{"front": "Strategic Architecture", "back": "Broad, summary architecture providing an organizing framework for operational and change activity \u2014 enables direction setting at executive level."}, {"front": "Segment Architecture", "back": "Medium-granularity framework providing an organizing layer for operational roadmaps at program or portfolio level."}, {"front": "Capability Arc